data.title: Alnylam Pharmaceuticals' stock drops as it reports Q3 earnings: $2.90 EPS vs. estimated $0.75, $1.25B sales vs. $977.79M. Subpoenaed by U.S. Attorney for pricing disclosures.
data.description: Alnylam Pharmaceuticals Inc.'s (NASDAQ: ALNY) stock price has declined following the release of its third-quarter earnings report, where the company disclosed receiving a subpoena from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Massachusetts. The subpoena pertains to government price reporting for their products Amvuttra, Onpattro, Oxlumo, and Givlaari, focusing on fee and discount agreements with distributors. ALNY is facing downward pressure due to bearish market momentum. In Q3 of 2025, the company reported adjusted earnings of $2.90 per share, a significant improvement from a loss of 50 cents per share the previous year, surpassing analysts' earnings estimates of 75 cents per share. Quarterly sales amounted to $1.25 billion, marking a 149% increase year over year, which exceeded the consensus of $977.79 million. Total net product revenues grew by 103% (99% at constant currency), driven by the expansion of Amvuttra sales. For more details, refer to the complete article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Cigna predicts 2 years of margin strain in pharmacy benefit unit, stock drops. New rebate-free model to start in 2027.
data.description: Cigna Group's stock, traded under NYSE: CI, experienced a sharp decline following the company's third-quarter 2025 earnings call where it disclosed expectations of margin pressure in the pharmacy benefit services segment for the next two years. The stock, CI, displayed noticeable weakness. On Monday, Evernorth, the health services division of Cigna, revealed a new rebate-free pharmacy benefit model aimed at reducing costs and enhancing transparency. Cigna Healthcare is set to implement this model for its fully insured lives from 2027 onwards, and it will be the standard model for all Evernorth pharmacy benefits clients starting in 2028. The company mentioned during the earnings call that it has revisited the economic terms of contracts to alleviate financial strains for partners operating predominantly in government programs. Additional details on third-quarter 2025 revenue and analysis can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon shifts tone on crypto, acknowledges their significance. Bank to allow clients to use Bitcoin and Ethereum as loan collateral by 2025.

data.title: Germany's AfD suggests classifying Bitcoin as a strategic asset amidst EU's MiCA regulations, promoting digital sovereignty and financial innovation.
data.description: The political party AfD in Germany is pushing for Bitcoin to be recognized as a strategic asset, in direct opposition to the EU's MiCA regulations. This move is seen as an effort to enhance digital sovereignty and spur financial innovation. This challenge intends to redefine the classification of Bitcoin and potentially impact its standing within the regulatory framework. The AfD's stance could potentially influence the governance of digital currencies in the region, with Bitcoin emerging as a key player in the financial landscape. This decision could have implications for the wider cryptocurrency market and its integration with traditional financial systems.

data.title: Crypto majors dip after Fed hints at uncertainty. BTC -3% at $110,100, ETH -3% at $3,900. MegaETH nets $1.25B in ICO. Fed cuts rates by 25 bps. OpenAI eyes $1T IPO by 2026. Mastercard eyes up to $2B acquisition. Senators criticize Trump's crypto stance.
data.description: Major cryptocurrencies experienced losses following the FOMC's uncertain guidance and a successful meeting between Trump and Xi. BTC fell by 3% to $110,100, ETH dropped by 3% to $3,900, BNB increased by 1% to $1,120, and SOL decreased by 2% to $192. ZEC surged by 9%, and AERO by 7%. The Federal Reserve Board lowered interest rates by 25 bps and announced the end of QT on Dec 1, with Powell suggesting a December rate cut was not guaranteed. The likelihood of one more rate cut in 2025 dropped from 84% to 67% after Powell's statements. OpenAI revealed plans for a $1 trillion IPO by H2 2026. Michael Saylor remains bullish on BTC, aiming for $150k by year-end. Mastercard intends to acquire blockchain startup Zero Hash for up to $2 billion. Consensys (Metamask) is preparing for an IPO with JPMorgan and Goldman as leads. Ethereum launched a new website focusing on ecosystem data for institutions. Senators Warren and Sanders criticized the Trump administration's crypto-related moves in 401(k)s, citing investor risks. Bitchat by Jack Dorsey ranked first in Jamaica's App Store for social networking amid Hurricane Melissa.

data.title: Neil Smith retires after 20+ years at U.S. Sugar, Rob Lyke promoted to VP of Savannah Sugar Refinery.
data.description: In Clewiston, Florida, U.S. Sugar revealed the retirement of Neil Smith, Senior Vice President of Sugar Manufacturing and President of the Savannah Sugar Refinery, after serving the company for over 20 years. Rob Lyke has been appointed as the new Vice President of the Savannah Sugar Refinery, taking over Smith's responsibilities. Smith's contributions to operational excellence at U.S. Sugar were highlighted in the announcement.

data.title: Vivakor sells $2.7M of common stock & pre-funded warrants to an investor for gross proceeds; 13M shares and 2M warrants issued.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Vivakor, Inc. announced a deal with one institutional investor to sell 13,000,000 common stock shares valued at $0.001 per share and 2,000,000 pre-funded warrants at $0.001 per share. data.title: University of Phoenix showcases Women in Cybersecurity with 500+ members during National Cybersecurity Awareness Month.
data.description: In Phoenix, the University of Phoenix is emphasizing its Women in Cybersecurity (WiCyS) Student Chapter as part of National Cybersecurity Awareness Month, showing their dedication to supporting opportunities in cybersecurity careers. Established recently, the chapter has surpassed 500 members, demonstrating the university's focus on assisting students in developing expertise, self-assurance, and networking within the cybersecurity industry. The program aims to empower women to pursue cybersecurity professions by providing resources and building a supportive community.
